fields.value: Behavioral data for "A functional connectome phenotyping dataset including cognitive state and personality measures"

authorAffiliation.value: Max Planck Institute for Human Cognitive and Brain Sciences
Max Planck Institute for Human Cognitive and Brain Sciences

dsDescriptionValue.value: This dataset enables exploration of higher-order cognitive faculties, self-generated mental experience, and personality features in relation to the intrinsic functional architecture of the brain. 194 healthy participants (between 20 and 75 years of age) filled out 31 questionnaires, performed 7 tasks, and reported 4 probes of in-scanner mind-wandering. This dataset constitutes one part of the Leipzig Study for Mind-Body-Emotion Interactions database, and contains the behavioral measures for download.
